name: Food Pantry Lax
review_text: Great place to come and get weekly snacks if you find yourself houseless like myself. The staff are great, barring one female staff member for, whom I think, eyes me with the "I don't think he's truly a houseless person eye". To that, I say to myself: "One should not judge another by appearance alone" For even though I am truly houseless, I work hard to, and to keep my stature and appearance up, and that may throw some viewees off. I just simply feel that one (not) has to be filthy, wrinkled, down, dirty and/or decrepit to be a houseless individual. Enough said. I do so appreciate LAX PANTRY and all they do and have done.
